One important correction is emerging: D3D11 `DrawIndexed` is submitted immediately after `applyPreDrawState`, not queued by this plugin, but CPU/GPU execution is still asynchronous. That means the hazard is not “recorded draw later looks up current offset”; it is “later Map/rename/reuse can affect resource storage while earlier commands are still in the GPU queue,” plus any state-cache issues.
