codex
A second, more concrete suspect is visible in the shared-ring API itself: `getNumberOfLockableDynamicVertices(false)` reports free capacity, and `lock()` uses the requested count as the mapped length. With the accounting fix, `CuiLayerRenderer` now regularly maps almost the entire remaining ring with `NO_OVERWRITE`, even though it only intends to reserve scratch capacity. That pattern is D3D9-compatible, but it is a poor D3D11 contract for a single shared dynamic resource because D3D11 map ranges are not explicit and the plugin has no separate “reserved” vs “committed” state.
