codex
I’m correcting my earlier phrasing: D3D11 `Map` does not take a byte range, so “huge mapped span” is not itself something the driver enforces. The length still matters to this ring allocator’s wrap decision, but the D3D11 contract is really per-resource plus the caller’s promise not to overwrite in-flight bytes.
