codex
I found a concrete point to verify against your “UI unlocks actual” premise: the engine wrapper may maintain its own vertex count apart from the backend data. If the wrapper leaves the count at the lock maximum while only the backend commits the actual count, UI quad-list draw count could explode. I’m reading that now because it would exactly explain “D3D9-faithful backend fix made full-screen black triangles worse.”
